Use this data source to get the ARN of a certificate in AWS Certificate
Manager (ACM), you can reference
it by domain without having to hard code the ARNs as input.


<div><pulumi-examples>

package main

func main() {

		_, err = acm.LookupCertificate(ctx, &acm.LookupCertificateArgs{

<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="domain_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#domain_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Domain</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Domain of the certificate to look up. If no certificate is found with this name, an error will be returned.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="keytypes_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#keytypes_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Key<wbr>Types</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>List of key algorithms to filter certificates. By default, ACM does not return all certificate types when searching. See the <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/acm/latest/APIReference/API_CertificateDetail.html#ACM-Type-CertificateDetail-KeyAlgorithm">ACM API Reference</a> for supported key algorithms.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="mostrecent_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#mostrecent_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Most<wbr>Recent</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>If set to true, it sorts the certificates matched by previous criteria by the NotBefore field, returning only the most recent one. If set to false, it returns an error if more than one certificate is found. Defaults to false.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="statuses_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#statuses_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Statuses</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>List of statuses on which to filter the returned list. Valid values are <code>PENDING_VALIDATION</code>, <code>ISSUED</code>,
<code>INACTIVE</code>, <code>EXPIRED</code>, <code>VALIDATION_TIMED_OUT</code>, <code>REVOKED</code> and <code>FAILED</code>. If no value is specified, only certificates in the <code>ISSUED</code> state
are returned.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="tags_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#tags_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Tags</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Mapping of tags for the resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">

        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>List of types on which to filter the returned list. Valid values are <code>AMAZON_ISSUED</code>, <code>PRIVATE</code>, and <code>IMPORTED</code>.</p>
